<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10142g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10142g">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10142g"> 142(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> drink 1<sup>st</sup> / die 1<sup>st</sup> <font color="green">[ius]</font> 1 noctis</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Reeking of resultant aroma Africanum, you may now have your first sip, for has he not guaranteed the said water pure from poison, as saith their proverb, <mark>&ldquo;Drink first, die first&rdquo;</mark>? <small> Daniel Crawford, <a name="DCTB" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#DCTB"><cite title="source">Thinking Black</cite></a> (1912) 71-2</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: L. Jus primae noctis. The right of the first night, also known as the droit du seigneur. The supposed feudal right exercised by a lord of having sexual intercourse with the bride of his vassal on the wedding night. </mm> </dd></dl>
